WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:13.346 --> 00:16.391
[theme music playing]

00:29.237 --> 00:31.156
[Ani] <i>Do innocent people run?</i>

00:32.615 --> 00:33.615
<i>They do,</i>

00:34.034 --> 00:35.452
<i>if that's their only choice.</i>

00:36.036 --> 00:38.830
[Caleb, whispering] No fucking way
are you driving to Mexico today.

00:38.997 --> 00:40.665
And you're definitely not taking Clay.

00:40.749 --> 00:42.935
[Tony] He can stay at my family's
till things cool down.

00:42.959 --> 00:45.240
- [Caleb] You didn't do anything.
- [Tony] Neither did he!

00:45.503 --> 00:46.503
[Caleb] Tony!

00:50.383 --> 00:53.720
You've got to start thinking
of yourself, Tony. Of your future.

00:53.803 --> 00:55.243
That's exactly what I'm thinking of.

00:55.930 --> 00:58.808
[Caleb] You let that kid drag you down.
You've done it before.

00:58.892 --> 01:00.351
He's my friend!

01:01.102 --> 01:02.228
And he needs me.

01:02.312 --> 01:03.146
[Caleb] I need you!

01:03.229 --> 01:05.829
[Tony] You're not the one who's wanted
for a murder you didn't do.

01:05.857 --> 01:07.734
How do you know he didn't do it?

01:23.541 --> 01:26.002
[Mrs. Jensen]
<i>Do you have any idea where Clay is?</i>

01:27.837 --> 01:28.880
I have no clue.

01:29.380 --> 01:31.216
When I came home last night,
he wasn't there.

01:31.299 --> 01:32.467
And what time was that?

01:33.384 --> 01:34.384
Around midnight.

01:34.761 --> 01:37.472
When I woke up this morning,
his bed was still made.

01:37.555 --> 01:40.225
I tried calling his phone,
but then I remembered the cops took it.

01:40.308 --> 01:42.560
And he gave you no indication
that he intended to flee?

01:43.520 --> 01:45.730
- No warning at all.
- Well, can you blame him?

01:45.855 --> 01:49.025
The police just kicked down our door,
for Christ's sake. He's scared shitless.

01:49.109 --> 01:52.695
Justin, I know that you and Clay protect
each other, but if there's something

01:52.779 --> 01:54.989
- you're not telling us...
- I don't know anything.

01:55.573 --> 01:56.574
I swear. I...

01:58.451 --> 02:00.203
He clearly didn't want me to know.

02:01.246 --> 02:03.331
[Ani] <i> Justin was as good as his word.</i>

02:03.706 --> 02:07.544
He would defend Clay until the end.
Which was going to get complicated.

02:09.044 --> 02:10.755
[Standall] Or Clay would defend Justin.

02:11.256 --> 02:12.340
Or Tyler Down.

02:12.423 --> 02:15.135
Or Jessica Davis. Or Zach Dempsey.

02:16.553 --> 02:19.139
[Ani] <i>As a fugitive,
Clay had one weakness.</i>

02:19.764 --> 02:21.349
<i>He cared about other people.</i>

02:24.894 --> 02:25.728
Hey.

02:25.812 --> 02:27.730
Clay, what are you doing here?

02:27.814 --> 02:29.399
I came to say goodbye. I'm...

02:30.316 --> 02:32.152
I'm leaving.
I don't think I'm coming back.

02:32.819 --> 02:33.987
But that's crazy.

02:34.529 --> 02:35.923
- They'll find you.
- If I stay here,

02:35.947 --> 02:37.147
it's not gonna get any better.

02:37.198 --> 02:39.033
Think it through.
There's going to be a trial.

02:39.117 --> 02:42.138
- Your lawyers will find things we missed.
- The cops have made up their minds.

02:42.162 --> 02:44.622
- So, we'll unmake them.
- [scoffs] How will we do that?

02:45.999 --> 02:46.999
I'll...

02:47.709 --> 02:48.709
I'll be your alibi.

02:49.127 --> 02:52.005
I'll say that I was with you
and that I didn't come forward before

02:52.088 --> 02:54.465
'cause of my mum,
and that you and I were together.

02:55.049 --> 02:56.209
And that we kept it a secret.

02:56.259 --> 02:59.512
Look, I'm not gonna point at Tony
or Justin or anyone else. I'm...

02:59.971 --> 03:02.599
- And I'm sure not gonna let you do that.
- Clay, you have to.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.100
I gotta go.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.895
- Clay, please.
- Look, I love that you want to help me,

03:07.228 --> 03:09.748
but you will get found out somehow
and you'll be in big trouble.

03:10.023 --> 03:11.823
And I know your mom's
not speaking to you now,

03:11.858 --> 03:14.319
but you're all she has
and you can't do that to her.

03:18.698 --> 03:19.532
I really gotta go.

03:19.616 --> 03:20.616
Clay...

03:39.010 --> 03:40.011
This isn't over.

03:48.519 --> 03:49.604
[speaking in Swahili]

03:50.980 --> 03:52.440
[speaking in Swahili]

04:11.167 --> 04:12.168
He what?

04:12.919 --> 04:16.547
Holy shit! Justin... [stammering] Wait.
So, he's just gone?

04:18.925 --> 04:21.010
Yeah, if I see him, I'll call you,
but I...

04:21.803 --> 04:23.388
Okay, yeah. Okay.

04:24.305 --> 04:25.682
[Monty] Was that Justy?

04:25.765 --> 04:27.868
He have an excuse
why he skipped weights this morning?

04:27.892 --> 04:30.353
- Yeah, family stuff.
- [scoffs] He doesn't have a family.

04:30.853 --> 04:33.481
Wait, who's gone? Jensen?
What the fuck? Did he take off?

04:34.190 --> 04:35.608
What? Why would he do that?

04:35.817 --> 04:37.485
Holy fuck, maybe he <i>is </i> guilty!

04:37.568 --> 04:40.571
He's not guilty, that's insane.
There's no way he could've taken on Bryce.

04:40.780 --> 04:42.865
You know what?
That would've taken someone who was,

04:42.949 --> 04:47.662
I don't know, six foot, one-ninety,
nasty fucking temper.

04:48.621 --> 04:50.748
Sounds like someone
I wouldn't want to fuck with.

04:55.753 --> 04:56.754
Come on, Charlie.

05:11.352 --> 05:12.562
[cell vibrating]

05:13.938 --> 05:16.482
- Uh, hello?
<i>- Hey, Tyler. It's Clay.</i>

05:17.817 --> 05:20.820
I wanted to let you know I can't drive
you home today. I won't be at school.

05:21.195 --> 05:22.195
[Tyler] <i>Oh,</i>

05:22.530 --> 05:23.740
<i>you won't be at school?</i>

05:23.948 --> 05:25.533
[Clay sighing] Yeah.

05:25.825 --> 05:29.829
So, maybe you can hitch a ride
with Alex or someone?

05:30.413 --> 05:31.413
Okay, um...

05:31.831 --> 05:34.709
but I mean, I was really hoping
you'd be here today.

05:34.792 --> 05:36.127
<i>There's this assembly.</i>

05:36.336 --> 05:37.337
Yeah, I just...

05:39.464 --> 05:40.798
I can't, man. Okay?

05:41.799 --> 05:42.800
Yeah, okay.

05:45.261 --> 05:46.763
<i>You're gonna be all right, yeah?</i>

05:47.680 --> 05:48.680
Yeah.

05:49.098 --> 05:50.098
I just...

05:50.683 --> 05:52.393
<i>I was really hoping you'd be here.</i>

05:53.353 --> 05:54.562
<i>Today of all days.</i>

05:54.979 --> 05:55.979
Why me?

05:56.773 --> 05:58.399
<i>What do you mean "of all days?"</i>

05:58.900 --> 06:00.276
Because I needed a friend.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.360
[car horn blowing]

06:05.073 --> 06:06.073
Tyler...

06:06.824 --> 06:07.824
ah... [sighing]

06:08.576 --> 06:11.329
Listen, I gotta run, but I'll try, okay?

06:15.291 --> 06:21.255
Welcome, everyone. And a very special
welcome to our guests from Hillcrest.

06:22.340 --> 06:24.342
We would like this to be a time...

06:25.176 --> 06:26.386
to come together.

06:27.261 --> 06:29.430
The interruption of our Homecoming game

06:30.014 --> 06:33.184
inflamed feelings on all sides.

06:33.726 --> 06:35.728
And it was followed a few days later...

06:36.646 --> 06:38.731
by the news of the tragic death

06:38.815 --> 06:42.026
of a former Liberty
and recent Hillcrest student,

06:42.110 --> 06:43.152
Bryce Walker.

06:43.820 --> 06:44.987
Now, I've spoken at length

06:45.071 --> 06:49.784
with the student leadership,
and Hillcrest administrators.

06:50.284 --> 06:53.746
We agreed that it was time
to bring our schools together

06:54.789 --> 06:56.833
for a day of accountability and healing.

06:57.375 --> 06:58.668
And with that in mind...

06:59.710 --> 07:00.711
Jessica Davis,

07:01.212 --> 07:04.632
student body president
and organizer of the protest,

07:05.466 --> 07:06.968
would like to offer a few words.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.095
[applause]

07:13.015 --> 07:15.643
Thank you, Principal Bolan.
You're absolutely right

07:15.977 --> 07:17.478
that at times like these,

07:17.854 --> 07:20.690
people need to be held accountable
for their mistakes.

07:20.982 --> 07:25.069
And after something traumatic happens,
it's important to focus on healing.

07:27.822 --> 07:28.865
But the thing is...

07:30.575 --> 07:32.743
how is anybody supposed to heal

07:32.827 --> 07:36.330
if all we do is cover up the wounds
and hope that they'll go away?

07:41.002 --> 07:44.964
We have to look at them
and recognize them for what they are.

07:46.591 --> 07:47.842
We have to be honest

07:47.925 --> 07:50.720
about who actually got hurt and how.

07:56.350 --> 07:58.811
The protest I led was an attempt

07:58.895 --> 08:02.231
to try to draw attention
to the rape culture in boys' sports

08:02.690 --> 08:04.233
and throughout our school.

08:04.525 --> 08:05.525
And yes,

08:05.985 --> 08:09.071
I admit that
the way I went about it wasn't perfect.

08:10.239 --> 08:12.909
I'm sorry for how it all ended up.
I really am.

08:13.951 --> 08:17.914
But making mistakes is part
of being a survivor.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.958
At first, you think you're, like...

08:21.918 --> 08:23.044
permanently broken.

08:24.712 --> 08:25.712
But then...

08:27.340 --> 08:28.424
little by little,

08:29.008 --> 08:30.843
you start picking up the pieces

08:30.927 --> 08:34.722
and you start realizing
what you're making is a mirror.

08:35.306 --> 08:36.306
And...

08:36.682 --> 08:38.683
the more of those pieces
that you put together,

08:38.768 --> 08:41.187
the more you start to see yourself.

08:43.688 --> 08:44.524
But maybe

08:44.607 --> 08:47.985
we can start picking up those pieces
of that mirror together,

08:48.069 --> 08:50.655
and we can finally see the truth.

08:52.031 --> 08:55.493
If you think sexual assault
doesn't affect your life, you're wrong.

08:56.285 --> 08:59.580
There are survivors all around us.

09:00.206 --> 09:02.500
People you care about...

09:03.751 --> 09:06.879
who you never knew
were suffering in silence.

09:08.798 --> 09:10.925
Let them know that you're there to listen.

09:12.426 --> 09:14.136
It's time for you to know

09:14.845 --> 09:16.472
the survivors in your life.

09:16.556 --> 09:19.976
To hear their stories
and to know that their voice matters.

09:24.313 --> 09:26.065
My name is Jessica Davis,

09:27.275 --> 09:28.442
and I'm a survivor.

09:29.735 --> 09:31.195
[crowd whispering]

09:33.281 --> 09:35.825
My name is Casey Ford,
and I'm a survivor.

09:38.035 --> 09:39.745
[Ani] <i>Jessica was fearless.</i>

09:40.496 --> 09:43.791
My name is Janelle Martin,
and I'm a survivor.

09:49.422 --> 09:50.881
[Ani] <i>And her courage spread.</i>

09:50.965 --> 09:52.216
My name is Maggie Kim,

09:52.300 --> 09:53.426
and I'm a survivor.

10:12.028 --> 10:13.028
[girl gasps]

10:13.321 --> 10:14.739
[shakily] My name is Tyler Down...

10:16.532 --> 10:17.658
and I'm a survivor.

10:20.703 --> 10:22.705
[crowd murmuring]

10:26.500 --> 10:27.710
My name is Lina Ochoa,

10:28.919 --> 10:30.087
and I'm a survivor.

10:30.880 --> 10:32.465
[Ani] <i>It went beyond her group.</i>

10:32.590 --> 10:33.966
My name is Sarah Stern.

10:35.134 --> 10:36.177
I'm a survivor.

10:41.223 --> 10:42.516
My name is Robby Corman...

10:44.727 --> 10:45.811
and I'm a survivor.

10:50.399 --> 10:52.276
My name is Tanya Brown.

10:53.152 --> 10:54.153
I'm a survivor.

11:01.702 --> 11:03.454
My name is Justin Foley...

11:07.875 --> 11:08.918
and I'm a survivor.

11:16.550 --> 11:20.596
My name is Stephanie Rodriguez,
and I am a goddamn survivor.

11:20.971 --> 11:21.971
[girl] Yeah!

11:22.973 --> 11:25.434
[scattered applause]

11:28.688 --> 11:30.981
[Ani] <i>Jessica was totally fearless
that day.</i>

11:32.108 --> 11:35.319
<i>She acted like someone who didn't care
about the cost of courage.</i>

11:35.569 --> 11:37.863
To those of you who are still seated,

11:38.739 --> 11:42.284
I know a lot of you still have stories,
but you're not ready to share them yet.

11:42.368 --> 11:43.953
And that's okay.

11:44.578 --> 11:46.205
When you're ready, we'll listen.

11:46.747 --> 11:50.334
And we will continue to fight
to make sure that no one

11:50.418 --> 11:54.171
is assaulted, harassed or abused
at this school.

11:55.464 --> 11:58.092
We will not sit down.
We will not be quiet.

11:58.175 --> 12:00.594
We will not rest until that happens.

12:07.560 --> 12:08.560
Yeah!

12:11.814 --> 12:14.066
- [cheering]
- [indistinct shouting]

12:21.866 --> 12:23.951
[cheering]

12:29.540 --> 12:31.709
- [Jessica] I'm so proud of you!
- [Tyler] Thank you.

12:32.376 --> 12:34.086
Hey, Jessica. Can I talk to you?

12:34.253 --> 12:35.963
- See you.
- [Tyler] Yeah, see you.

12:37.339 --> 12:38.339
[Robby] Um...

12:38.424 --> 12:40.968
- hey, it's Tyler, right?
- Yeah, hey.

12:41.385 --> 12:43.763
Um... nice to meet you, Robby.

12:44.054 --> 12:46.182
Thank you for being the first.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.226
[stammering]
I mean... first guy to stand up.

12:49.810 --> 12:51.103
Yeah. I mean...

12:52.021 --> 12:53.021
for sure.

12:53.230 --> 12:55.441
Do you think I could be a part
of HO, too?

12:56.192 --> 12:58.068
Is that... allowed?

12:58.360 --> 12:59.361
Fuck, yeah!

12:59.779 --> 13:02.239
It's more than allowed.
Everybody's welcome at HO.

13:02.531 --> 13:03.532
Fucking everybody!

13:04.033 --> 13:06.994
Even if some people were dicks to them
in the beginning.

13:08.496 --> 13:09.705
Some people are sorry.

13:14.877 --> 13:15.753
- Hey.
- Hey.

13:15.836 --> 13:17.338
That was... incredible.

13:17.421 --> 13:18.672
You were incredible.

13:18.756 --> 13:21.050
Thank you. I was so freaked out, but...

13:21.801 --> 13:23.427
I'm so happy I did it.

13:23.677 --> 13:26.055
Seeing all those people stand up,
it was...

13:26.138 --> 13:28.098
I loved that bit in your speech
about the mirror.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.559
Is that from something, or...

13:31.060 --> 13:32.228
Why, what do you mean?

13:33.229 --> 13:36.023
Well, nothing, it was just...
It was really beautiful.

13:36.774 --> 13:39.944
And I was just wondering
if it was... something you'd heard before,

13:40.820 --> 13:42.154
or if it just came to you?

13:42.238 --> 13:44.698
I don't know.
I guess it just kind of came to me.

13:46.992 --> 13:49.662
- I should...
- Yeah, of course. Congrats.

13:49.745 --> 13:50.745
Thanks.

13:52.873 --> 13:56.377
[Ani] <i>I guess I wondered where
that fearlessness might have come from.</i>

13:57.503 --> 14:00.339
I just, uh, I wanted to ask
if you were okay?

14:00.881 --> 14:02.049
If you needed anything?

14:02.883 --> 14:05.469
No, man. I'm good at the moment.
But thank you.

14:05.719 --> 14:08.639
What happened to me
didn't... didn't happen today.

14:08.722 --> 14:10.266
No. I mean, I know.

14:10.724 --> 14:11.724
Um...

14:12.059 --> 14:13.060
yeah, listen...

14:14.061 --> 14:15.145
I'm sorry, man.

14:15.896 --> 14:17.940
And I think...

14:18.607 --> 14:19.775
I think you're awesome.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.654
Yeah, Charlie. Thank you.

14:26.156 --> 14:28.033
- Shit. I gotta go.
- Yeah.

14:30.244 --> 14:31.244
Hey.

14:32.288 --> 14:33.414
You made it.

14:34.331 --> 14:37.418
Tyler, listen, man.
I gotta take off. But, um...

14:40.296 --> 14:41.589
I'm so proud of you.

14:41.672 --> 14:42.672
Yeah?

14:43.465 --> 14:44.592
Thank you.

14:45.467 --> 14:46.867
Clay, where the fuck have you been?

14:47.177 --> 14:48.012
I have to go.

14:48.095 --> 14:50.848
- Are you fucking crazy? You can't run.
- [Jessica] Justin.

14:51.473 --> 14:52.600
Was that real just then?

14:52.683 --> 14:54.268
- Yes. Yeah...
- [Sheriff] Clay Jensen!

14:55.978 --> 14:56.978
[door closing]

14:59.648 --> 15:00.649
[Sheriff] Clay Jensen,

15:01.358 --> 15:03.903
I have a warrant for your arrest
for the murder of Bryce Walker.

15:04.486 --> 15:06.246
Turn around.
Put your hands behind your back.

15:08.449 --> 15:09.491
Clay! I...

15:10.034 --> 15:11.474
You have the right to remain silent.

15:11.535 --> 15:14.788
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

15:15.289 --> 15:17.750
You have the right to an attorney.
If you cannot afford one,

15:18.334 --> 15:20.628
one will be appointed to you
by the court.

15:21.211 --> 15:22.211
Let's go.

15:29.261 --> 15:31.597
[Ani] <i>The Sheriff was convinced
he had his man.</i>

15:34.433 --> 15:35.643
But you weren't so sure.

15:36.477 --> 15:37.477
[Standall] No.

15:40.105 --> 15:41.649
[chatter]

15:41.982 --> 15:43.901
[Mrs. Walker]
So, why don't you give that a try?

15:43.984 --> 15:44.984
[woman] Okay.

15:45.319 --> 15:48.030
Yeah, I think you'd enjoy it.
Okay. Thanks.

15:48.113 --> 15:49.113
[woman] Okay.

15:49.907 --> 15:50.907
Deputy.

15:51.533 --> 15:53.202
- Good morning.
- Morning, ma'am.

15:54.370 --> 15:55.204
Is there news?

15:55.287 --> 15:57.414
Well, the Sheriff is close
to having a case

15:57.498 --> 16:00.000
he feels he can turn over
to the county prosecutor.

16:00.084 --> 16:02.962
But there's just a few things I'd like
to confirm with you, if I may?

16:03.253 --> 16:04.463
Of course.

16:04.546 --> 16:06.006
Do you have any reason to believe

16:06.090 --> 16:08.300
that Clay would purchase steroids
from your son?

16:08.884 --> 16:09.885
I, um...

16:10.970 --> 16:12.137
Not that I can recall.

16:12.221 --> 16:14.598
But Clay did purchase marijuana
from Bryce once?

16:15.683 --> 16:17.559
I think that was just a pretense.

16:18.060 --> 16:20.521
To get into our home. To entrap Bryce.

16:20.604 --> 16:24.483
Okay, other than that
and the incident in the driveway,

16:24.566 --> 16:27.987
did Bryce ever spend any time with Clay
that you can remember?

16:29.905 --> 16:30.948
Not that I knew of.

16:31.740 --> 16:33.450
They weren't friends, of course.

16:33.534 --> 16:36.745
Well, who did Bryce spend time with
in that time after he left Liberty?

16:37.579 --> 16:38.579
Well, um...

16:39.748 --> 16:40.833
Montgomery de la Cruz

16:40.916 --> 16:43.544
was over a number of times last summer,
and...

16:45.796 --> 16:46.922
your son.

16:47.464 --> 16:48.966
They seemed close for a while.

16:49.591 --> 16:50.591
Uh-huh.

16:50.843 --> 16:52.678
Yeah, I knew
they spent some time together.

16:52.761 --> 16:53.761
But...

16:55.305 --> 16:59.601
Bryce really didn't have any friends left
these past months.

17:01.270 --> 17:02.896
All he had was me, really.

17:06.567 --> 17:09.444
[Mrs. Walker] <i>Press down
through that left big toe mound.</i>

17:09.528 --> 17:12.448
Roll the chest open. Exhale. That's it.

17:12.531 --> 17:14.700
Shoot that tailbone
towards your right heel.

17:14.782 --> 17:16.910
Beautiful. How's that feel? Breathe.

17:18.579 --> 17:20.289
Good. Come on down.

17:21.248 --> 17:22.374
Does that feel better?

17:22.458 --> 17:23.751
- Good. Thank you.
- Thanks.

17:26.502 --> 17:27.628
Good class, Teach.

17:28.589 --> 17:29.423
[sighs]

17:29.548 --> 17:32.092
Teacher-in-training.
I'm still finishing my hours.

17:32.217 --> 17:33.969
Still, that's some tough-looking shit.

17:35.137 --> 17:36.137
Stuff.

17:36.597 --> 17:38.640
Sorry. Sacred space.

17:38.724 --> 17:40.184
Not sacred, but...

17:41.393 --> 17:42.393
spiritual, I hope.

17:43.520 --> 17:44.646
[chuckles]

17:44.897 --> 17:46.023
Don't laugh!

17:46.106 --> 17:47.191
