believe me.

18:29.441 --> 18:30.943
Lift your hips up and back.

18:32.194 --> 18:34.988
Stretch your heels to the floor.
Lift your sit-bones.

18:35.906 --> 18:37.746
Your hamstrings are too tight.
Bend your knees.

18:37.783 --> 18:39.543
It's more important
to have a straight spine.

18:41.537 --> 18:45.165
Breathe. Every breath takes you deeper
into the pose.

18:45.249 --> 18:46.583
[Bryce breathing deeply]

18:46.959 --> 18:49.419
Okay, good.
Now we're going to move into pigeon.

18:50.546 --> 18:52.881
- Sorry. [chuckling]
- It's all right.

18:53.507 --> 18:56.301
On an inhale,
raise your right leg up and back.

18:56.802 --> 18:57.636
Okay.

18:57.719 --> 19:01.473
As you exhale, right knee to right wrist.
Lay your shin down.

19:03.725 --> 19:06.895
Good. Slide that foot forward.
But protect your knee.

19:07.813 --> 19:09.231
Stretch your left leg back.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.066
Square your hips.

19:12.985 --> 19:15.362
Good.
Take a deep breath in, lift your heart.

19:15.487 --> 19:16.530
[both inhaling]

19:16.738 --> 19:19.908
As you exhale,
see if you can lengthen out over that leg.

19:21.743 --> 19:22.953
Do that a couple times.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.247
[groaning]

19:27.583 --> 19:29.168
Good. This opens up your hips.

19:30.335 --> 19:31.628
Uh...

19:32.004 --> 19:33.922
- [grunting] this is hard.
- Okay.

19:34.381 --> 19:37.467
It's important to go slow
and respect the body's boundaries.

19:37.885 --> 19:39.553
Wait till the body gives you permission

19:39.636 --> 19:41.096
to go deeper, don't force.

19:41.430 --> 19:42.514
[exhaling]

19:44.975 --> 19:45.975
Good.

19:54.943 --> 19:55.986
[Mrs. Walker] Good.

20:06.330 --> 20:08.582
[sobbing]

20:11.210 --> 20:12.711
You're shaking. Does it hurt?

20:14.379 --> 20:16.006
Inhale. Lift your torso.

20:18.217 --> 20:19.301
Oh, Bryce.

20:21.511 --> 20:22.512
I don't know what...

20:23.263 --> 20:25.891
I don't know what's happening,
I just started crying.

20:25.974 --> 20:28.268
It's okay. It's good. It's okay.

20:29.436 --> 20:32.272
- I don't know why I can't stop.
- It's okay.

20:35.859 --> 20:37.361
[sobbing]

20:38.028 --> 20:39.071
[whimpering]

20:56.213 --> 20:57.214
They aren't mine.

21:00.592 --> 21:02.512
Do I look like the kind of kid
who uses steroids?

21:02.552 --> 21:04.304
Why hide them in your drawer, then?

21:06.723 --> 21:07.724
I was holding them.

21:10.018 --> 21:11.061
For a friend.

21:11.478 --> 21:12.478
